  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life-saving distribution of emergency food items for the most vulnerable IDP and host community</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Yirol East State has received an additional 37,000 IDPs since October 2016, as reported by the RRC (Relief and Rehabilitation Commission) of Yirol East (January 2017). Adior reportedly has a host population of 15,000 and 11,000 IDPs, while Pagarau, with a population of 9,000 hosts 6,000 IDPs.
This displacement is significantly exacerbating the severe food insecurity. Unusual dry spells, late and inconsistent rains in 2016 have caused a shortage of food stocks. While stocks under normal circumstances sustain the population from harvest in August to May of the next year, followed by a hunger gap in June and July, this year stocks have already run out in January, hitting both IDP and host community to a life threatening level. Newly arrived IDPs were not able to grow any food and many households have been surviving on leaves in the absence of alternative food sources. With harvest still 5-6 months away and aid not reaching the targeted areas, the most vulnerable stand little chance to survive.</narrative>
  </description>
